                    Overview:



A growing U.S.-based personal injury law firm is seeking 2–3 dedicated, self-driven Remote Client Intake Specialists to handle new client calls and sign-ups during overnight U.S. hours and full weekend coverage. This is not a basic answering service role — you will be the firm's first impression and a critical driver of its growth. We take client experience seriously and are looking for professionals who do too.



You will be given full authority to close new clients independently, walking them through the firm's services, obtaining signed retainer agreements electronically, and entering all case information into our system — all without attorney involvement.

This is a commission-eligible role. Top performers will earn meaningfully above their base hourly rate.



Coverage Hours (U.S. Central Time):



Shifts are assigned across the following coverage windows. Each worker will be assigned an approximately 40-hour weekly schedule within these hours:



Monday – Friday: 6:00 PM – 10:00 AM CT (overnight/after-hours coverage)

Saturday & Sunday: Full 24-hour coverage



Note: All times correspond to U.S. Central Time. Please confirm your availability for overnight and weekend shifts before applying.



Primary Responsibilities – Client Intake & Closing:



Serve as the first point of contact for potential new clients (PNCs) calling the firm after hours, on weekends, or during call overflow;

Conduct thorough intake interviews by phone to gather all necessary case information, including i
 details, injuries sustained, insurance coverage, and current medical treatment;

Evaluate case viability based on firm criteria and make independent sign-up decisions;

Clearly and professionally explain the firm's services, contingency fee structure, and client expectations;

Secure signed retainer agreements and medical authorizations electronically — independently, without attorney involvement;

Enter all client and case information into CASEpeer (our case management CRM) promptly and accurately;

Collect and upload all supporting documentation including police reports, insurance declarations, and medical provider information;

Follow up with potential clients who have not yet signed, using empathetic and persuasive communication;

Track your own conversion metrics and flag patterns or opportunities for process improvement.





Secondary Responsibilities – Prelitigation Support:



Assist with scheduling initial medical appointments for newly signed clients where applicable;

Ensure new client files are complete and transition-ready for the daytime case management team;

Coordinate signed authorizations and document requests from clients;

Communicate with insurance adjusters as needed to confirm claims are opened and policy limits have been requested;

Support smooth file handoffs from intake to the prelitigation team each morning.





Tools You Will Use:



CASEpeer – Case management and CRM (training provided; prior experience is a strong plus);

Zoom VOIP – All client calls are handled via Zoom's phone system;

Standard
 and electronic signature platforms for retainer execution.





Performance Expectations:



Maintain a strong conversion rate on potential client sign-ups;

Ensure 100?curacy in CASEpeer data entry and documentation;

Minimize lead drop-off through timely, effective follow-up;

Deliver complete, transition-ready files to the daytime team each shift;

Provide regular reporting on new sign-ups and pending leads.





Compensation:



Base Pay: $3.00 – $6.00 USD per hour, based on experience and qualifications;

Commission: Earned per successfully signed case meeting firm criteria — paid on top of hourly rate;

High performers have significant earning potential above base through commissions.





Ideal Candidate:



Excellent spoken and written English — clear, professional, and confident on the phone;

Spanish language ability is a plus but not required;

Prior experience in personal injury intake, legal client services, insurance claims, or medical intake strongly preferred;

Persuasive and empathetic communicator — able to earn the trust of injured clients in a first call;

Highly organized and detail-oriented with strong CRM data discipline;

Comfortable working independently with minimal supervision during overnight and weekend hours;

Reliable internet connection and a quiet, professional remote work environment;

Familiarity with U.S. legal processes or personal injury law is a significant advantage.





Why This Role:



You won't be reading from a script at a call center. You'll be representing a firm that genuinely cares about its clients and its reputation. You'll have real responsibility, real closing authority, and real earning potential tied to your performance. If you're experienced, motivated, and take pride in doing client-facing work the right way — we want to hear from you.
